pageTitle: Saturday expo helps residents get ready for disaster | CedarKeyBeacon.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {34080=Copyright © 2015, 25824=The Levy County Public Safety & Hurricane Preparedness Expo, sponsored by the Levy Department of Public Safety, will be Saturday, May 19, from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. at the Williston Airport. Admission is free. There will be demonstrations of vehicle extrications using the Jaws of Life, and working dogs for Search & Rescue and the Sheriffs’ Office. Displays will include ambulances, fire trucks, helicopters, hazardous materials equipment, police cars, a medical simulator lab, and forestry equipment from several counties. There will be booths from organizations — each providing those in attendance with valuable information to keep you and your family safe. Children won't be bored with activities geared towards them, including a bounce house., 26617=EXPO DEMONSTRATIONS 11 a.m. - Extrication Demonstration by Fire Department 1 p.m. - Extrication Demonstration by Fire Department 2 p.m. - North Central Florida Intra Agency K-9 Demonstration 2:30 p.m. - Extrication Demonstration by Fire Department}
